# OpenHachimi Agent

This project is your own agent application built on top of
[PydanticAI](https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic-ai).

## Why this setup

- You do **not** need to fork `pydantic/pydantic-ai` to build your own agent.
- The upstream project uses the MIT License, so you can build your own app on top
  of it as long as you keep the original license notice when you copy upstream
  source code into your own project.
- The cleanest approach is to keep your app in its own repository and install
  PydanticAI as a dependency.

## Local setup

Use Python 3.10+.

```powershell
C:\Users\diyun-pc\.pyenv\pyenv-win\versions\3.13.2\python.exe -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -U pip
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -e .
Copy-Item .env.example .env
```

Then set your API key in `.env`.

## Run

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe .\main.py
```

## Recommended workflow

1. Keep this project as **your own repo/app**.
2. Use `pydantic-ai-slim[openai]` unless you need many providers.
3. If you want to study upstream internals, clone `pydantic/pydantic-ai`
   separately as a reference repo, but do not develop your app inside it.
4. Only copy upstream code into your repo when you truly need to customize
   framework internals. If you do, preserve the MIT license notice.
